.:: Puzzle 2x5-Level-8-4::.
There 5 different types of food: pear, mango, apricot, lime, asparagus
The people use 5 different means of transport: van, taxi, quad-bike, airplane, bus
 1. the person eating pear is somewhere between the person eating mango and the person driving the van##7
 2. the person driving the quad-bike is in an odd position##4
 3. the person driving the quad-bike is somewhere to the right of the person driving the taxi##5
 4. the person eating pear is somewhere to the right of the person driving the bus##5
 5. the person driving the van is on the far left##1
 6. the person driving the taxi is not the person eating apricot##6
 7. the person eating mango is on the right of the person eating pear##1
 8. the person eating asparagus is on the left or right of the person eating lime##3
 9. the person driving the taxi is somewhere between the person eating apricot and the person eating pear##7
10. the person driving the taxi is not to the right of the person eating mango##8
11. the person eating lime is the person eating lime##1
12. the person driving the taxi is not the person eating lime##6
13. the person driving the airplane is on the right of the person eating lime##1
14. the person eating lime is somewhere to the right of the person eating apricot##5

.:: Answer ::.
|               |   1    |   2    |     3      |     4     |     5     |
| Food   | apricot | asparagus | lime | pear | mango |
| Transport           | van    | taxi | bus    | airplane      | quad-bike      |

